rachel-hong.content: Rachel Hong studied math econ at the University of Pennylvania and graduated in 2017. She's currently working at Crossix in New York, originally from San Jose, California. She has previously interned at Blue Shield of California, the Federal Reserve Bank of San Francisco and Ernst & Young. In her free time, she enjoys overpriced exercise classes, reading, and hiking. Rachel joined Hack4Impact in its first semester and has served on the executive board as community chair.
